    "replaced large-size filters (5 × 5 and 7 × 7) with small and asymmetric filters (1 × 7 and 1 × 5) and used 1 × 1 convolution as a bottleneck before the large filters (Szegedy et al. 2017). layers.",
    "ResNet, on the other hand, maintains greater accuracy while having 152 layers in its depth.",
    "ResNet alludes to the highway network concept Srivastava et al. (2015) and is composed of stacked residual blocks.",
    "The structure of a residual block is illustrated in Fig. 21.",
    "In addition to containing weighted layers, a residual block directly connects the input x to the output through a shortcut connection."
